        "comment": "The avalanche risk is moderate above 1600 metres. Wet snow is the problem. Gliding avalanches can occur on a few steep slopes with a smooth surface, such as meadow slopes or rock slabs. In addition, loose snow or slab avalanches can release themselves on extremely steep terrain or be triggered by individuals on very steep terrain. The avalanches are wet and reach medium size.",
        "highlights": "There is still a lot of snow on the northern sides in some places."
