      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "It may snow a little at higher altitudes. Occasionally, smaller snowdrift accumulations in areas adjacent to the ridgeline, crest or summit may be prone to triggering. The old snowpack is generally very moist to wet up to the higher elevations and consists mainly of snowmelt. Only on north-facing slopes can layers of faceted crystals still be present deep in the snowpack. The new fallen snow melts quickly on the apery ground on the southern slopes."
      },
